								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>Richard likes his current OS very much, except for one thing: it's not written by him. Bit by bit, he wants to replace the parts of his current OS with his own code. His ultimate aim is to have an identical copy of his host OS, but with his code. Maybe you prefer a <a href="What_order_should_I_make_things_in" title="What order should I make things in">different approach</a>
</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc"><tr><td><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="Richard_Theseus#Pro.27s_.26_Con.27s"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Pro's &amp; Con's</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="Richard_Theseus#Going_further_than_Richard"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Going further than Richard</span></a></li>
